            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The school denied admission to my daughter due to her mild ADHD, despite her being intelligent and performing well academically. They stated that they do not have special educators, which goes against government guidelines on inclusive education.\n\nThere may also be another reason for the rejection, possibly related to religion. Noida is often perceived as having bias against the Muslim community, and this could have influenced their decision.\n\nI am writing to the education authorities to highlight how such practices are affecting children today. I am aware that no action may be taken, but I believe it is important to raise awareness about these biases. It is concerning that institutions responsible for educating children may themselves lack an understanding of equality.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
